  "_meta": {
    "purpose": "Type-descriptor overrides for fields NattKh's pabgb_complete_schema.json leaves as stream=?/type=?. Ported from Potter420/crimson-rs (MIT) src/item_info/item.rs. Resolves the 22 unknown-stream fields in ItemInfo so the parser can walk past them to reach _cooltime and the 70+ fields after it.",
    "source": "https://github.com/potter420/crimson-rs/blob/main/src/item_info/item.rs",
    "license": "MIT — credit Potter420 (corin) per crimson-rs LICENSE",
    "format": "Each table key may also have a special `_ordered_fields` array listing the deserialization order. When present, the loader REPLACES NattKh's field array with this order (NattKh's array is sorted by memory address, NOT serialization order). Field-level overrides set type descriptors. Verified empirically against vanilla iteminfo.pabgb 2026-04-27.",
    "added_2026_04_27": "Path B coverage: ItemInfo (113 fields), VehicleInfo (19), FieldInfo (19 of 26 — _complexData blocks the rest), StageInfo (81 of 82), RegionInfo (24), CharacterInfo (14-field mount subset). 6 tables, ~270 fields total."
  },
